  "rationale": "<p style=\"text-align: left;\">The correct answer is <math alttext=\"StartFraction 189 Over 5 EndFraction\"><mfrac>\n<mn>189</mn>\n<mn>5</mn>\n</mfrac>\n</math>. A <em>y</em>-intercept of a graph in the <em>xy</em>-plane is a point where the graph intersects the <em>y</em>-axis, which is a point with an <em>x</em>-coordinate of <math alttext=\"0\"><mn>0</mn>\n</math>. Substituting <math alttext=\"0\"><mn>0</mn>\n</math> for <math alttext=\"x\"><mi>x</mi>\n</math> in the given equation yields <math alttext=\"StartFraction 3 left parenthesis 0 right parenthesis Over 7 EndFraction equals minus StartFraction 5 y Over 9 EndFraction plus 21\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mfenced><mn>0</mn></mfenced></mrow><mn>7</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>5</mn><mi>y</mi></mrow><mn>9</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mn>21</mn></math>, or <math alttext=\"0 equals minus StartFraction 5 y Over 9 EndFraction plus 21\"><mn>0</mn><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>5</mn><mi>y</mi></mrow><mn>9</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mn>21</mn></math>. Subtracting <math alttext=\"21\"><mn>21</mn>\n</math> from both sides of this equation yields <math alttext=\"negative 21 equals minus StartFraction 5 y Over 9 EndFraction\"><mo>-</mo><mn>21</mn><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>5</mn><mi>y</mi></mrow><mn>9</mn></mfrac></math>. Multiplying both sides of this equation by <math alttext=\"negative 9\"><mo>-</mo><mn>9</mn>\n</math> yields <math alttext=\"189 equals 5 y\"><mrow>\n<mn>189</mn>\n<mo>=</mo>\n<mrow>\n<mn>5</mn>\n<mi>y</mi>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n</math>. Dividing both sides of this equation by <math alttext=\"5\"><mn>5</mn>\n</math> yields <math alttext=\"StartFraction 189 Over 5 EndFraction equals y\"><mrow>\n<mfrac>\n<mn>189</mn>\n<mn>5</mn>\n</mfrac>\n<mo>=</mo>\n<mi>y</mi>\n</mrow>\n</math>. Therefore, the <em>y</em>-coordinate of the <em>y</em>-intercept of the graph of the given equation in the <em>xy</em>-plane is <math alttext=\"StartFraction 189 Over 5 EndFraction\"><mfrac>\n<mn>189</mn>\n<mn>5</mn>\n</mfrac>\n</math>. Note that 189/5 and 37.8 are examples of ways to enter a correct answer.</p>",
